<subSubSection id="DCCBBC87FFF400756892F890FEEE8999" pageId="31" pageNumber="532" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="946EEF0CFFF400756892F890FEEE8999" blockId="31.[151,1436,1860,2030]" pageId="31" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="A6A5331EFFF400756892F890FEE78929" bold="true" box="[151,274,1860,1886]" pageId="31" pageNumber="532">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
SIF = 7BS-N-3-3111.1000; fsp = 7.7.7; fCx = 1.1.1; fSt = 2.2; fPp = B/B/NNB; fSc: PL&gt; AM&gt; AL; Ip = 607–637; fD = 2H-6(7)-6-4-2(2-4)+(2–6); DS = 30–32; V = 26–30; NDV = 57–60. Scutum nearly trapezoidal, with large anterolateral shoulders and sparse puncta; sensilla with ca. 10 branches in distal two thirds; sensillary bases slightly anterior to level of PL (PSB—P-PL = 2–6 µm). Standard measurements of examined specimens given in 
<tableCitation id="D953DAB7FFF4007568B6F800FEE28999" box="[179,279,2004,2030]" captionStart="TABLE 10" captionStartId="32.[151,239,152,176]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="TABLE 10. Morphometric (AW–dmt, µm; m-t—ratio) and meristic (DS–NDV) traits of Parasecia valida (n = 10)." pageId="31" pageNumber="532">Table 10</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
